What drives individuals to achieve success is a highly personal combination of past experiences and expectations. No two people have experienced the exact same set of circumstances in their lives, therefore they cannot both define success exactly the same.

Competition drives each person to success by their individual motivations. While sometimes, team cooperation and success of a team can be a motivating factor for an individual, it is not the only factor. C
while cooperation may only require a contributor to be \"as good\" as the others they are working with. \n

While cooperation and teamwork are clearly important to be a successful individual, it is competition that drives the internal desire to win that creates the success. People will achieve more success by participating in competiton against their peers rather than simply cooperating with others.
